HEADWORD: Prehension
<hw>Pre*hen"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>prehensio</ets>; cf. F. <ets>pr⟦eacute⟧hension</ets>. See
<er>Prehensile</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of taking hold, seizing, or
grasping, as with the hand or other member.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prehensory</ent>⟦br⟧
